cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.DM, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper discusses the equivalence of HDAs from a logical and topological perspective.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with the abstraction of a computational model.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the equivalence of different models of computation, which is relevant to programming language design.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with the homotopy type and homology graph of HDAs, which are concepts from discrete mathematics.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses conditions under which cube collapses yield topological abstractions of HDAs, which could be relevant to the computational complexity of the abstraction process.
